track_notes: Park at the Little Elbow parking lot just before the campground. Biking along the Big Elbow trail to the South Glasgow Creek is recommended (to save almost 8km of walking). Once you reach the creek, follow the creek bed until the end of the end of the valley by the large hill of shale. Hike up the scree slope up to the ridge. From here, hike along the ridge to Mount Glasgow. Continue back along the ridge towards Mount Cornwall, Outlaw Peak, and Banded Peak. After summiting Banded Peak, follow the north ridge down towards the valley. Hike along the upper plateau (above the river) to lookers left (hiking east). Hike all the way back to the Big Elbow trail and back to the Little Elbow parking lot.
track_title: Mount Glasgow, Mount Cornwall, Outlaw Peak, and Banded Peak traverse
